---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE, GAME } from '../consts';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: SITE.url },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Cheats', item: new URL('/cheats', SITE.url).href },
  ],
};
---
<Base
  title="Moonlight Peaks Cheats & Console Commands"
  description="Moonlight Peaks cheats and console commands: how the cheat console works and the full money, skill, and item command list — published at launch on July 7, 2026."
  path="/cheats"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Cheats' }]}
>
  <article class="page">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Entry · Cheats</p>
      <h1>Moonlight Peaks <em>cheats</em> & console</h1>
      <p class="intro">
        The complete command list goes live the day {GAME.title} launches ({GAME.releaseLabel}).
        Here's what to expect and how cheat consoles in cozy life sims usually work. Updated {SITE.updated}.
      </p>

      <h2>Is there a cheat console?</h2>
      <p>
        It is not yet confirmed which player-facing cheats {GAME.title} will ship with — that's
        only knowable once the full game is out. Cozy life sims in this space commonly include a
        console you open with a key combo, then type a command such as a money grant or a skill
        boost. The moment the game launches we will document the exact key, the verified commands,
        and any caveats (for example, whether cheats disable achievements).
      </p>

      <h2>Published at launch</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>How to open the console</strong> — the exact key combo, PC and Switch where applicable.</li>
        <li><strong>Money commands</strong> — the verified codes to add currency.</li>
        <li><strong>Skills, needs, items</strong> — the full categorized list, with one-tap copy.</li>
        <li><strong>Warnings</strong> — save-stability and achievement notes.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="callout wip">
        We will not invent commands. Everything here is sourced from the live game or the developers
        — if it's not verified, it won't be listed. Check back on {GAME.releaseLabel}.
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
